    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-09-23T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-09-23T06:00:00-05:00" n="488"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d488">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">880.00/9–2347: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-09-23T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 23, 1947—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4118. With reference to my several telegrams concerning my talks with the French
                    on subject of North African situation I have now received from Chauvel a
                    complete Foreign Office folder (including memorandum and 25 detailed appendices)
                    on French policy concerning Moroccan and Tunisian protectorates.</p>
                <p>I consider that the information contained in these papers is on the whole most
                    encouraging and generally in line with the recommendations of North African
                    meeting held Paris June 16–19, 1947.</p>
                <p>Detailed analysis going forward by airmail despatch<note n="1" xml:id="d488fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Infra</hi>.</note> within 4 hours and full report<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d488fn2">See despatch 9644, September 19, <hi rend="italic"
                            >supra</hi>.</note> as soon as possible thereafter.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 4118, repeated Tangier 38, Rabat 19, Tunis 23, Algiers 71.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
